nadia: You made it through. But you're not in the city anymore.
nadia: This is the first layer of the internet — the public web. The surface.
nadia: In the real world, it looks like a screen full of apps and bright promises. In here, you see it for what it is.
nadia: Those creatures that look like Bats? They're Spam Bots. Automated. Endless. They flood every corner of this place.
nadia: They were designed after the gambling ads that started this whole crisis. Same psychology. Same flashing patterns. But faster, and multiplied across millions of devices.
nadia: Don't trust anything that flashes and makes promises. That's how the trap works — out there AND in here.
nadia: The signal we're tracing goes deeper. Much deeper than this layer.
nadia: Keep moving.
